# berriz-os conventions

## Before doing anything

Read `AGENTS.md` at the repo root. It contains the folder map, the task guide,
and the list of things NOT to do in this repo.

## Source of truth rules

- `projects/projects.yaml` is the source of truth for the project index.
  Always update the YAML; then update `projects/index.md` to match.
  Never edit `index.md` without also editing `projects.yaml`.

- `brand/narrative.md` is the source of truth for all public-facing copy.
  Never invent new bio text or taglines — use or adapt variants from that file.

- `brand/voice.md` governs all writing in this repo and any content drafted on
  Alejandro's behalf. Read it before writing any public-facing copy.

## What belongs here vs. elsewhere

- Personal OKRs, career planning, salary notes → `atlas` (private repo, NOT here)
- New project repos → sibling directories in `~/repos/`, NOT subdirectories of berriz-os
- New AI skills → `~/repos/agent-skills/`, NOT here
- Knowledge base content → `~/repos/intelligence-layer/`, NOT here

## Git conventions

Follow the process-git skill:
https://github.com/aleberriz/agent-skills/tree/main/plugins/core-skills/skills/process-git/SKILL.md

- Branch for every unit of work: `type/short-description`
- Conventional commits: `type: imperative description`
- Open a PR for every branch, even in solo work
- Default merge strategy: squash merge

## Tooling decisions

Check `brand/foss-posture.md` before recommending a new tool, dependency, or
hosting provider. Default to FOSS and Cloudflare Pages / Hetzner Cloud.

## Time-series naming

- Quarterly docs: `YYYY-QN-<slug>.md` (e.g., `2026-Q2-okr-review.md`)
- Newsletter issues: `YYYY-MM-DD-<slug>.md` (e.g., `2026-05-01-semantic-layer-intro.md`)
- Plans and roadmaps: `YYYY-<slug>.md` (e.g., `2026-personal-brand.md`)
